        "email": "green@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "green"
      },
      "date": "2011-06-13 23:44:31.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3: Looks good to me, approved\n\nThis looks good to me.\nI think using LU_PAGE_SIZE would be enough just on the client side. Though I guess guessing page size of the server might become tricky then?",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
    {
      "id": "3b4f820e68cfdd6d48bfb45347e6f89319385177",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 101,
        "name": "Lai Siyao",
        "email": "lai.siyao@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "laisiyao"
      },
      "date": "2011-06-14 01:58:21.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\nOleg, the reply dir entries are packed with page size LU_PAGE_SIZE, so the only requirement here is both server and client CFS_PAGE_SIZE bigger than LU_PAGE_SIZE (this should always be true):\n* on server size, only LU_PAGE_SIZE will be used to store lu_dirpage inside a *page, and this lu_dirpage will be packed into reply buffer.\n* on client, if necessary several lu_dirpage in reply buffer will be combined into one dir page.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
